Elevate your career in law enforcement technology and join us to make
Queensland the safest state – apply now and make a real impact!

** The core capability requirements for this role are: **

• Conduct analysis of business requirements and evolve those requirements for
technical design and implementation of solution components.  
• Apply governance processes to ensure the quality assurance of technical
products delivered by suppliers.  
• Translate business requirements into functional and technical specifications
incorporating analysis of maintainability, scalability, security,
supportability, usability and other non-functional requirements.  
• Define key test scenarios and carry out verification testing to ensure the
solution is complete and meets agreed business requirements.  
• Provide support to builders and testers to ensure the required solution
outcomes are achieved, including assistance with documentation and testing of
defect fixes and changes.  
• Provide advice on database, desktop, infrastructure (server and operating
system), infrastructure (virtualisation and storage), mobility, software and
telecommunication solutions, products and services to internal and external
stakeholders.

** Role Requirements **

** Technical/ Operational/ Educational experience **

Highly desirable

• Experience with the SDLC  
• Experience in one or more of the following technical specialities:  
• Database  
• Desktop  
• Infrastructure (server and operating system)  
• Infrastructure (virtualisation and storage)  
• Mobility  
• Software  
• Telecommunications

Desirable

• Use of fit-for-purpose tools to record and manage requirements for the
documentation and management of quality assurance.  
• System analysis activities on complex Commercial-Off-The-Shelf (COTS)
products  
• Knowledge of Agile delivery  
• Awareness of ITIL framework or similar process methodologies  
• Awareness of PRINCE2 and similar project management methodologies  
• A degree level qualification in Information Technology or Computer Science

Other

This position may be required to:

• Perform some duties after-hours on a scheduled basis  
• Perform on-call support outside of regular business hours

SFIA Skills

• The following technical criteria reflect relevant professional skills and
competencies from the Skills Framework for the Information Age (SFIA)
Framework relevant to this role:  
• Level: 5  
• Skill Code(s)  
• BUSA: Business Situation Analysis

Further information can be found on the SFIA site by searching for the ‘skill'
code (e.g. ITMG) and then referring to the skills listed under the applicable
‘level' e.g. level 5

